                <section class="project_recipe">
                    <header>
                        <h1>How to get my street cleaned up in San Francisco</h1>
                        <h2>by <a href="#">FAQ Robot</a></h2>
                    </header>
                    <ol class="recipe_steps">
                        <li>
                            <p>Call 311 to see if people are already involved with cleanups on your street via the Adopt-A-Street program.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Recall that the law requires property owners/ground floor tenants to keep their adjacent sidewalk clean of trash and leaves. Contact 311 if there is a violation.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Attempt to join San Francisco’s <a href="http://www.sfdpw.org/index.aspx?page=1229">Adopt-A-Street Program</a>.</p>
                            <p>Organize merchants and neighbors on your street. They all have a strong incentive to see the street cleaned.</p>
                            <p>If you are an individual, you can make an agreement with San Francisco to clean up your street. Merchant and neighborhood associations can also make an agreement with San Francisco to clean up a street.</p>
                            <p>(If you are having trouble finding volunteers or other partners, contact an organization like A Good Idea - <a href="http://agoodideasf.org/">http://agoodideasf.org</a>. They may be able to connect you with willing volunteers.)</p>
                            <p>The Department of Public Works will provide supplies for you (e.g., brooms, rakes, bags, gloves).</p>
                            <p>To sign up for the Adopt-A-Street program, email <a href="mailto:volunteer@sfdpw.org">volunteer@sfdpw.org</a> or fill out this form: <a href="http://38.106.4.205/ftp/uploadedfiles/sfdpw/director/Adopt_a_Street_(application_only).pdf">http://38.106.4.205/ftp/uploadedfiles/sfdpw/director/Adopt_a_Street_(application_only).pdf</a></p>
                            <p>Send your application form to:<br />2323 Cesar Chavez Street<br />San Francisco, CA 94124-1091</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Once you have organized a day to clean up your street, you and your volunteers can call 311 to request a pickup of your garbage.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>
                
